{"questionId":"9c629a63-5faf-46a6-929d-d4196f7c3150_6","correctAnswer":"3","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Factor the second equation","content":"Rewrite: $\\dfrac{cx}{3y}=\\dfrac{c}{3}\\cdot\\dfrac{x}{y}=87$."},{"title":"Combine and compute","content":"Substitute $\\dfrac{x}{y}=87$: $\\dfrac{c}{3}\\cdot 87=87$, so $\\dfrac{c}{3}=1$ and $c=3$.<br/><br/>The answer is <strong>3</strong>."}]}